Lyrics:
We were staring down disaster
That night we almost called it quits
You said that you were changing chapters
I said this can’t be where it ends
Not even poetry can fix this
Right now we both need more than words
If we give up we’re gonna miss this
Can we remember who we were
 
Standing on St Brigid’s road 
Where we finally let it go 
 
We held a funeral for heartache
We buried trouble in the grass
We didn’t bother buying roses
Cause we ain’t going back 
I don’t know nothing bout tomorrow
I barely know about today 
We set a fire to our sorrow
And watch the hurt go up in flames
 
Grief is such a solid promise
Joy just leaves you in the rain 
Sadness waits down in the lobby
Solace stood you up again 
I’m thankful for the darkness
Every thing it let me see
So much beauty in the storm 
Like how you turned to me
If I’m honest you’re the reason
That the light gets in at all 
You’re the song that breaks the silence
You’re the smile at curtain call
I’m scared of who I’d be without you 
Much more than you know
If I seem strong it’s just a show
 
Standing on St Brigid’s road
Where we finally let it go 
 
We held a funeral for heartache
We buried trouble in the grass
We didn’t bother buying roses
Cause we ain’t going back 
I don’t know nothing bout tomorrow
I barely know about today 
We set a fire to our sorrow
And watch the hurt go up in flames
 
Oh no, no, we ain’t ever going back

We didn’t bother buying roses
Cause we ain’t going back 
I don’t know nothing bout tomorrow
I barely know about today 
We set a fire to our sorrow

snippet.title: He-Man: Masters Of The Universe - Teaser Trailer (2026) Nicholas Galitzine | Amazon MGM | Concept
snippet.description:
— Attention Viewers ⚠️
— This is a Fan-Made Concept Trailer for:
— He-Man: Masters Of The Universe

— This video is a fan-made concept trailer, created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes.The goal behind this trailer is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through a concept trailer based on a unique and original idea. By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I’ve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Masters of the Universe, the legendary saga is reimagined as a grounded, character-driven story of identity and destiny. Prince Adam, portrayed by Nicholas Galitzine, begins his journey on Earth, unaware of his true heritage as the alien prince of Eternia. As his past resurfaces, Adam must embrace his transformation into the powerful He-Man, stepping into a role of leadership and responsibility amidst a brutal conflict led by the menacing Skeletor, played by Jared Leto. With a star-studded cast, including Camila Mendes as Teela and Idris Elba as Man-At-Arms, this adaptation delves into Adam’s struggle to balance his humanity with his newfound destiny, weaving a tale of power, family, and sacrifice. The trailer captures the intense emotional journey of a reluctant hero discovering what it means to wield true power, all set against the backdrop of a war-torn world that demands his courage.

—  For inquiries: teaseruniverse@gmail.com 📩

Prince Adam, portrayed by Nicholas Galitzine, begins his journey on Earth, unaware of his true heritage as the alien prince of Eternia. As his past resurfaces, Adam must embrace his transformation into the powerful He-Man, stepping into a role of leadership and responsibility amidst a brutal conflict led by the menacing Skeletor, played by Jared Leto. With a star-studded cast, including Camila Mendes as Teela and Idris Elba as Man-At-Arms, this adaptation delves into Adam’s struggle to balance his humanity with his newfound destiny, weaving a tale of power, family, and sacrifice. The trailer captures the intense emotional journey of a reluctant hero discovering what it means to wield true power, all set against the backdrop of a war-torn world that demands his courage.

About Creedence Clearwater Revival: 
Creedence Clearwater Revival’s 1968 self-titled debut album introduced the world to guitar-playing brothers John and Tom Fogerty, drummer Doug Clifford, and bassist Stu Cook, four young men out of El Cerrito in the San Francisco Bay Area. Though they emerged in a place and time where trippy psychedelic visions were the order of the day, CCR bucked the trends and instead tapped into a rich, traditional seam of American music that connected to blues, country, rockabilly, gospel, folk and R&B.    

During their short time together as a band (1968 – 1972), the band enjoyed an unparalleled period of creativity lead by singer, songwriter, arranger John Fogerty. They’ve sold close to 100 million records, releasing 14 Top 10 hits. They also managed to play over 150 tour dates around the world, including a headlining spot at Woodstock.

Creedence Clearwater Revival’s canon has become a part of the Great American Songbook. Fogerty penned songs like “Bad Moon Rising,” “Down on the Corner,” “Fortunate Son,” “Have You Ever Seen the Rain,” “Proud Mary,” “Born on the Bayou,” “Travelin’ Band” and “Up Around the Bend” have been ingrained into pop culture — not just as rock staples, but as classic standards.

With so many memorable songs that continue to grace our radio waves, television and movie screens, plus lyrics that still resonate today, Creedence Clearwater Revival is, truly, America’s greatest rock ’n’ roll band.

#ccr #creedenceclearwaterrevival #fortunateson

snippet.title: Reptile (2026) - First Look | Jason Statham, Dwayne Johnson - Concept Trailer
snippet.description:
#Reptile2026 #JasonStatham #DwayneJohnson

Watch This Reptile Fan Made Concept Trailer (2026)

Jason Statham brings lethal precision to a black ops soldier who's exposed to experimental serum during a mission gone wrong, granting him the ability to regenerate limbs, blend into environments like a chameleon, and survive injuries that would kill normal humans. Statham plays Marcus Cole, a former special forces operative who becomes living weapon with reptilian DNA fused into his cells, creating superhuman abilities that make him invaluable asset and terrifying liability when the transformation starts affecting his psychology. Dwayne Johnson enters as General Hawkins, the military commander who orchestrated the experiment and now must decide whether Marcus is soldier who can be controlled or predator who needs to be eliminated before he goes completely feral. What makes this concept gripping is exploring the body horror of transformation where enhanced abilities come at the cost of losing humanity one scale at a time.

The visual effects showcase Marcus's reptilian features emerging during combat—vertical pupils dilating in darkness, skin shifting colors to match surroundings, clawed hands tearing through enemies with brutal efficiency that's more animal than soldier. You'll see brutal action sequences where Statham's natural physicality combines with CGI enhancement to create fighting style that's disturbingly inhuman, using walls and ceilings like a gecko while regenerating from wounds mid-battle. Johnson brings conflicted authority to a general who views Marcus as both greatest achievement and biggest mistake, someone who enabled this transformation knowing full well the ethical lines being crossed in pursuit of perfect soldier. The film explores dehumanization through sci-fi lens, asking what happens when military treats people as expendable experiments and whether anyone can maintain their soul when their body stops being human. Expect conspiracy thriller elements as Marcus hunts those responsible while evading capture, spectacular parkour-influenced combat utilizing his reptilian abilities creatively, and psychological horror watching someone fight to preserve identity when instincts are screaming to embrace the predator within.

Disclaimer:
This is an unofficial fan-made concept trailer created for entertainment and artistic purposes only. It is not affiliated with or endorsed by any film studios or production companies. This video uses AI-generated imagery and editing techniques to visualize a hypothetical original science fiction thriller.
